  "signature": "ed25519:9b1d3e7f2a04c6b8e1f5a3d07c2b9e4f6a8d1c3e5b7f0a2d4c6e8b1f3a5d7c9",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The simulation software (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2) must operate under a documented quality management system conforming to ISO 9001 or equivalent; version control, regression testing logs, and change-control records must be available for audit. Gradation 2 requires at minimum a documented QMS with traceable version history.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 is deployed under DePuy Synthes and FDA OSEL quality management systems both certified to ISO 13485. Software validation records, regression test suites, and change-control logs were reviewed and found current. Achieved level 3 reflects additional independent code-to-code benchmarking against ABAQUS for representative beam-column problems."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification must demonstrate that the solver correctly implements the governing equations for static structural analysis; patch tests and manufactured-solution comparisons for linear elastic continuum elements must be on record. Gradation 2 requires documented patch-test passage for all element types used.",
      "rationale": "Patch tests and manufactured-solution benchmarks for the hexahedral and tetrahedral element formulations used in the pedicle screw model were executed and archived in the project verification log (Doc. NVL-2023-04). All tests passed within machine-precision tolerances. Required level 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A formal mesh-convergence study must demonstrate that QoI values (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) change by less than 2% between the penultimate and final refinement levels. Gradation 3 requires Richardson extrapolation or equivalent GCI analysis.",
      "rationale": "A four-level mesh-refinement study was conducted on the screw shank and rod junction regions where stress gradients are highest. Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI values below 1.8% for all three QoIs. The production mesh (approx. 420 000 elements) was selected at the level where GCI dropped below the 2% threshold."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals must be driven below 1×10⁻⁶ for force and displacement norms; energy balance checks must confirm conservation to within 0.1%. Gradation 2 requires documented convergence monitoring for all submitted load steps.",
      "rationale": "All nonlinear load steps used a Newton-Raphson scheme with force and displacement convergence criteria set to 1×10⁻⁶. Energy balance was monitored via the Ansys OUTRES command; maximum energy imbalance across all runs was 0.04%. Solver log files are archived in the project repository."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model setup, boundary condition application, and post-processing scripts must be reviewed by an independent analyst; a documented peer-review checklist must be on file. Gradation 2 requires at minimum one independent reviewer sign-off.",
      "rationale": "An independent FEA analyst (not involved in model construction) performed a full peer review of the APDL input deck, boundary condition definitions, and post-processing scripts against the simulation plan. Review checklist (Doc. NUR-2023-07) was signed and archived. No critical discrepancies were identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The constitutive model selection (bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V) must be justified by literature evidence and confirmed by coupon-level calibration data. Gradation 3 requires material-coupon validation in addition to literature justification.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.14 GPa) was selected based on published Ti-6Al-4V data (MMPDS-12) and confirmed against DePuy Synthes internal coupon tensile tests (n=5). Friction at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces was modeled with μ=0.2 based on tribological literature for Ti-Ti contacts under dry conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and geometric dimensions used in the model must be traceable to measured values from the physical test specimens; dimensional metrology reports must be on file. Gradation 3 requires specimen-specific dimensional measurements rather than nominal CAD values.",
      "rationale": "Dimensional metrology (CMM) was performed on a representative subset of test specimens (n=3 per laboratory). Screw outer diameter, pitch, and rod diameter were confirmed within ±0.05 mm of nominal. Material certificates (Ti-6Al-4V, ASTM F136) were obtained for all screw lots. Model geometry was updated to reflect measured mean dimensions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation dataset must comprise at least 10 independent test specimens; specimens must be drawn from production lots with documented material traceability. Gradation 3 requires multi-laboratory testing with inter-laboratory reproducibility assessment.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs were tested across two independent laboratories (Lab 1: n=6; Lab 2: n=5). Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation for stiffness was 4.2%, for yield force 3.8%, and for force at 40 mm 5.1%, all within acceptable reproducibility bounds. Material traceability was confirmed for all 11 specimens."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation testing must span at least two distinct loading configurations or boundary condition variants representative of the clinical use envelope; single-condition testing is insufficient at Gradation 3. Gradation 2 is the highest achievable when only one standardized test configuration (ASTM F1717) is employed.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted exclusively under the ASTM F1717 static compression-bending configuration at a single displacement rate (5 mm/min) and a single vertebral body height (25 mm UHMWPE block). While the F1717 protocol is the regulatory standard for pedicle screw constructs, it represents a single idealized loading condition. The clinical loading environment encompasses axial compression, torsion, and lateral bending components not captured by this configuration. The assessment team acknowledges that Gradation 3 would require at minimum a second independent loading mode (e.g., torsion per ASTM F1717 or axial fatigue per ASTM F2193) to be included in the validation dataset. The gap is documented as a known scope limitation of this COU; the overall credibility assessment remains acceptable at the Medium assurance level because the model influence is Medium and the primary regulatory submission pathway relies on the F1717 result as a pass/fail gate rather than a predictive extrapolation to untested conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model boundary conditions, loading rates, and fixture geometry must be demonstrated to match the physical test setup within specified tolerances; deviations must be quantified and their effect on QoIs bounded. Gradation 3 requires sensitivity analysis on key boundary condition parameters.",
      "rationale": "Fixture geometry was reproduced in the FEA model from engineering drawings of the F1717 test apparatus. Sensitivity analyses on crosshead displacement rate (quasi-static assumption), fixture compliance, and UHMWPE block height (±1 mm) were conducted; QoI sensitivity was below 1.5% for all parameters. Boundary condition equivalency is confirmed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison must use a validation metric that accounts for experimental uncertainty; the E/uval metric (ASME V&V 40 Eq. 5-1) must be computed for each QoI and compared against the 1.96 threshold. All three primary QoIs must satisfy E/uval < 1.96.",
      "rationale": "E/uval was computed for stiffness (0.87), yield force (1.12), and force at 40 mm (1.44). All three values are below the 1.96 threshold, confirming that model prediction error is within the combined experimental and simulation uncertainty band at the 95% confidence level. The <10% relative difference criterion was also satisfied for all QoIs (maximum 6.3% for force at 40 mm)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) must be directly linked to the clinical failure mode of interest and to the regulatory submission QoIs. Gradation 2 requires a documented traceability argument from QoI to clinical endpoint.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly cited in the FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. Each QoI is mechanistically linked to the primary failure mode (plastic deformation or fracture of the screw shank under bending). Traceability matrix (Doc. NQI-2023-02) maps each QoI to the corresponding clinical risk scenario."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation activity must be conducted on the same device design and material system as the COU device; surrogate or scaled specimens are not acceptable at Gradation 3. The test configuration must match the intended regulatory submission context.",
      "rationale": "Validation specimens were production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws from the same design family and manufacturing process as the submission device. No surrogates or scaled models were used. The ASTM F1717 test configuration directly corresponds to the regulatory submission context for this device class. Relevance is rated at the highest achievable level for this COU scope."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/fda-cdrh-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single exception — Test conditions (achieved level 2 against required level 3) — is accepted under the Medium assurance level because the ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration is the primary regulatory standard for this device class and the model influence is Medium. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission decision. All three primary QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and the <10% relative difference criterion.",
